# Service Layer Rules

Services own business logic. Blueprints call services; services call models/engine/db.

## Responsibilities

- Orchestrate reads/writes and domain calculations.
- Keep methods testable without an HTTP request context when possible (app context may still be required for SQLAlchemy).
- Prefer returning models, dataclasses, or plain dicts — not rendered HTML.

## Curriculum-related services

- `CurriculumEngineService` — thin delegate to `CurriculumRepository` (no extra business logic).
- `CurriculumService` — DB import, progress, and **canonical traversal**.
- Other learning services must use `CurriculumService.get_all_topics_ordered` / `get_ordered_topics` / section helpers instead of ad-hoc ordering.

## Import / startup

- `CurriculumService.import_curricula()` must remain idempotent.
- `StartupService` must remain production-gated, exception-safe, and non-destructive.

## Do

- Pass `user_id`, model instances, and primitives explicitly.
- Log failures with context (exam/paper/version ids) without secrets.
- Keep one primary domain per service module.

## Do not

- Import `request`, `session`, or template functions inside services.
- Duplicate V1/V2 branching outside `CurriculumService` traversal/import helpers.
- Commit partial imports without clear transaction boundaries when creating related rows.
